<TITLE> Iniesta, Henry on course to play Champions League final </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BARCELONA, May 22 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Barcelona midfielder Andres Iniesta and striker Thierry Henry did light training on Thursday and are on course to play in Wednesday's Champions League final against Manchester United, the club said. Spain international Iniesta has a thigh problem and Frenchman Henry a knee injury but both have recovered enough to do ball work, the Primera Liga champions said on their website (www.fcbarcelona.cat). "I am convinced I will arrive in Rome in my best condition to be able to help the team," Iniesta said in a message posted on his personal website (www.andresiniesta.es)
